description:
File: rust/lichen-schc/src/codec.rs
Lines: 754-806 (decompress_mqtt_sn)

Category: CORRECTNESS

The decompress_mqtt_sn function receives data that was identified by rule_id in decompress(), but it does not verify that the address mode bit (addr_mode at line 758) is consistent with what the original packet would have encoded.

When compressing (line 502-514):
```rust
if is_link_local(src) && is_link_local(dst) {
    w.write(0, 1)?; // Address mode: 0 = link-local
    ...
} else {
    w.write(1, 1)?; // Address mode: 1 = full
    ...
}
```

When decompressing (line 760-773):
```rust
let (src, dst) = if addr_mode == 0 {
    // Link-local reconstruction
    ...
} else {
    // Full address read
    ...
}
```

If malformed compressed data has addr_mode=0 but the full addresses, the reconstructed packet would have link-local addresses (fe80::/64 prefix) appended to the IIDs, producing incorrect addresses.

Impact: Corrupted/malformed compressed data produces incorrect packets rather than errors.

Note: This is more of a robustness issue than a strict bug, since SCHC assumes well-formed compressed data from trusted sources.
